Capello said: &quot;Chinese owners of Milan and what they speak of? They do not talk much. Little is known . We talk, but there is no doubt about the Rossoneri future. We talk more about Inter, we are more involved there. It's a shame, and I'm telling it as sportsman and a man who worked for Berlusconi, that Milan finds himself in this situation after spending so much. &quot;  <br />
<br />
Capello said: &quot; No, I wanted trying to train another team at the end of my career. I was offered to rescue Suning and I succeeded. I would say the mission is accomplished. I still have a year of contract then I go on a vacation.&rdquo;

Milan CCO Lorenzo Giorgetti: &ldquo;We&rsquo;re negotiating with a big technical brand that&rsquo;s worthy of the 2nd most decorated club in the world.&rdquo;<br />
<br />
Giorgetti: &ldquo;The figures published by some press outlets does not correspond with the real ones. It won&rsquo;t be worse than the current deal.&rdquo;
